<define-tag description>security update</define-tag>
<define-tag moreinfo>
<p>Multiple security issues have been found in Icedove, Debian's version of
the Mozilla Thunderbird mail client: Multiple memory safety errors,
use-after-frees and other implementation errors may lead to the
execution of arbitrary code, the bypass of security restrictions or
denial of service.</p>

<p>For the stable distribution (wheezy), these problems have been fixed in
version 31.6.0-1~deb7u1.</p>

<p>For the upcoming stable distribution (jessie), these problems have been
fixed in version 31.6.0-1.</p>

<p>For the unstable distribution (sid), these problems have been fixed in
version 31.6.0-1.</p>

<p>We recommend that you upgrade your icedove packages.</p>
</define-tag>

